# Docker / OrbStack

OrbStack is the recommended local Docker runtime on macOS.
The project must remain standard Docker Compose compatible.

Use Makefile targets before raw docker compose commands.

Preferred local workflow:
- backend stack: `make up-backend`
- frontend local: `make web-dev`
- full stack only when needed: `make up` (no rebuild; use `make up-build` after image changes)
- optional scheduler (celery-beat): `make up-scheduler` (local `.env`) or `make shared-dev-up-scheduler` (`.env.shared-dev`)

Build / restart:
- backend image `houston-api:dev` (api + celery + celery-beat): `make build-backend`
- full stack images: `make build`
- bounce process (does not reload `.env`): `make restart-backend`
- after `.env` changes (recreates api/celery, `--no-deps`): `make recreate-backend`
- guard script tests (no DB): `make infra-check`

Shared-dev (remote PostgreSQL, `.env.shared-dev`):
- `make shared-dev-up` — runs compose preflight (`assert-shared-dev-compose.sh`) before `up`
- `make shared-dev-check` / `make shared-dev-bootstrap` / `make shared-dev-migrate`
- see `docs/engineering/shared_dev_database.md` (mode-switch checklist: `make down` then correct up target)
- never run `make reset-dev-db` or `make test` against shared-dev credentials in `.env`
- local `make up*` targets refuse remote DB (Compose-effective guard)
- mode switch: `make down` then `make up-backend` or `make shared-dev-up` — never assume `.env` alone retargets containers
- `make recreate-backend` does not switch modes (in-mode `.env` reload only)
- after shared-dev session: `make down` before `make test` / `make migrate` / `make reset-dev-db`

Do not run `docker compose up` without explicit service/profile unless requested.

Do not edit `.env` or introduce real secrets.
Edit `.env.example` only for documented configuration.

Do not commit or package:
- `.env`
- `.venv`
- `node_modules`
- `.git`
- `private_media`
- celerybeat runtime files
- caches

Use named volumes for container-owned runtime state:
- Postgres data
- frontend node_modules in Docker mode
- private media
- celerybeat schedule state

Do not bind-mount database data, node_modules, Python virtualenvs, or runtime media from macOS unless explicitly justified.

After dependency changes:
- backend: `make build-backend`
- frontend local: `make web-install`
- contract changes: `make schema && make web-api-generate`

Before final success:
- run the smallest relevant check first
- run `make verify` only for final confidence
